      "name": "Title and Text",
      "settings": {
        "title": "Botanica Collection - Inspired by the Bold Simplicity of Tulips",
        "text": "<p>There’s something quietly captivating about tulips. A familiar yet fleeting presence in British gardens, they herald the arrival of spring while carrying a rich and layered history. In Molly's latest <em>Botanica</em> collection, she revisits this iconic flower, translating its sculptural beauty into a refined series of luxury wallpapers and fabrics.</p><p>Inspired by the dramatic displays at Pashley Manor Gardens and the romantic planting at Great Dixter, the collection captures the tulip in all its bold simplicity - both structured and ephemeral, classic yet refreshingly modern.</p>",
        "font_type": "body",
        "vertical_alignment": "center",
        "alignment": "center",
        "color_scheme": "dark_text",
        "margin_top": "m",
        "margin_bot": "none"
      }
    },
    "image_with_text_axpBFx": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_7xGCbY": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "A Story Rooted in Craft & Heritage"
          }
        },
        "text_zdJW4K": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>At the heart of the <em>Botanica</em> collection is a thoughtful exploration of form and repetition. Each tulip is carefully framed, almost like a piece within a collector’s  gallery. This design approach nods to the Victorian passion for cataloguing the natural world, creating a sense of order and timelessness that translates beautifully into today’s interiors.</p><p>The result is a collection that feels equally at home in a traditional English country home or a contemporary interior seeking softness and depth. It’s decorative, but never overwhelming - elevated, yet effortlessly liveable.</p>",
            "code": ""
          }
        }
      },
